JUST LISTED - 5021 N Teresita Avenue in Meridian, Idaho

OPEN HOUSE 
Saturday, November 17th
12-3pm

Contemporary farm-style home in a prime location. The two-story residence features granite and quartz countertops, top-tier laminate flooring, detailed trim and loads of storage throughout. 

The bright and dreamy kitchen includes stainless steel appliances, a gas-burning range, a deep cast iron sink, polished chrome finishes, and a sizeable walk-in pantry. 

Natural light fills the main living area centered by a brick inlay high-efficiency gas fireplace. 

The master suite features a serene color scheme with a large walk-in closet, MAAX deep soaking tub, and dual vanity space. 

On the second level, the double-door entry gives way to a spacious bonus room and an additional bedroom with full bath. 

The backyard provides a private covered patio with outdoor fan and additional space is offered with an attached RV garage. 

Paramount community offers multiple common areas, multiple pools, parks, pathways, & clubhouse.

Visit https://aleimerrill.com/new-listing-for-sale/ or call Alei at 208-900-2534.

OPEN HOUSE - 4603 N Trotter Lane in Star, Idaho

Sunday, December 18th
12-3pm

An exceptional 10 Acres with 360 views ideally located between Star and Eagle. Beautiful, single-level home offers privacy and a multitude of amenities. 

Stunning endless views in all directions compliment the updated features. An inviting and warm interior complete with expansive oak flooring, a spacious open floor plan, and custom finishes.

Enjoy the floor-to-ceiling river rock fireplace. The bright kitchen features a large pantry and a wall oven unit. The owner’s suite has separate vanities, a deep soaking tub, and an oversized tile shower. 

Embrace the beauty of the Star foothills in the large backyard area with multiple entertaining areas, a large water feature, and the room to live the good life. 

This property features a 40x48 barn, four horse stalls, a riding area, and a fully irrigated fenced pasture. Separate 40x22 shop/RV garage with heated floors.

Visit AleiMerrill.com for more information.

🏡 OPEN HOUSE - 2620 N Hollybrook Place in Eagle, Idaho

Saturday, February 18th
12-3pm

5-acre Eagle equestrian estate surrounded by captivating mountain views and wide open spaces, a charming single-level home provides unspoiled solitude.

The enchanting and spacious home features expansive bright rooms, second primary suite, an inviting main living area, and stunning scenery from every window.

Precision metal fencing and gates specifically designed for multiple pasture areas. The gorgeous east-facing backyard provides tremendous comfort with an entertaining patio encircled by 42 mature timbered trees, a garden area, a variety of fruit trees, and a tranquil koi pond.

The large 44 x 48 barn provides two horse stalls, automatic water feeders, multiple tie posts, saddle stands, a mounting block, a tack room, a washing station, a workshop, and extensive storage and room for RV parking.

The exceptional full-size training arena and sprawling green hay pasture set the perfect backdrop for country living. Only 7 minutes from downtown Eagle amenities.

Visit AleiMerrill.com for more details or call Alei at 208-900-2534.
So proud to represent this pristine "Equestrian" home in one of my favorite 5-acre neighborhoods. Located near Floating Feather and Ballantyne in Eagle! Open House this SAT 12pm-3pm.

🏡 JUST LISTED 🏡 - 11610 W Lanktree Gulch Road in Star, Idaho

Elevated 10-acre lot overlooking green pastures where unobstructed northern mountain views and southern valley views prevail. Private drive leads to a charming single level home with circular driveway, vaulted ceilings, and window alignment to capture the beautiful Idaho scenery. The 42’ x 72 barn/shop is wired for a 50 amp and 240 amp, has multiple roll up doors with extensive parking for RV, trailers and cars.  Separate  office area with dedicated entrance. Four 12 x 12 horse stalls and corral areas make this an ideal equestrian property. Entire property has automatic sprinklers for low maintenance. 17 different types of producing fruit trees surround the shop area. Quiet, private, and serene describe this lifestyle property made for seeking the room to spread out and live the country experience.- yet only be a 5 minute drive to downtown Star or 15 minute drive to Eagle. Recreational opportunities to the north with close proximity to BLM land.
Coming soon, stay tuned 🙌🏼🤩
It’s always fun to be featured in the Eagle Magazine and this time I was able to do it with my two daughters! Big things coming with this powerful crew! My girls and I, we get stuff done 💪🏻
Big happy mama heart today 💗 it’s always fun to get all my family together but especially for a special occasion! Happy blessing day to our sweet baby Solace 😇

Eagle through the ages ✨ Did you know I’ve lived in Eagle since the population was only 368 people!? I’ve lived here my whole life and it’s crazy to see how much it’s grown! These displays hang in my office in the heart of downtown Eagle as a tribute to the Merrill legacy. I’m happy to answer any questions about living here in Eagle!

I can’t believe the season is halfway over! The nights may be freezing but there’s nothing better than seeing my kids do what they love. It makes all the hard work and long days worth it. I’ve made it a priority in my life to make it to every ball game. It can be hard when you own your own business, but isn’t that why you work so hard to begin with? To do the things you love with the people you love ❤️🙌🏼 #findyourwhy #aleisfabfive

Do Open Houses Work? (Many sellers have asked me that question over the years.) 

Well, this property was listed on a Thurs. with an Open House the next Sat. The first person through the Open House ended up being the new buyer. They did not even know about the house being on the market until seeing the Open House sign on State St., walking in, and falling in love. 

We went *PENDING* in only a few days....directly from the Open House! 

#openhouseswork #staridahorealestate

Visiting the Eagle Field of Honor yesterday I was reminded what an incredible place we live in. Grandpa Cheney on my Mom's side was the Veteran speaker at the first annual Field of Honor 17 years ago and I remember his tribute to those who served (including my other Grandpa). He wanted everyone to cherish the freedoms we have today. Thanks to all who make this event a reality and to those who have served our country valiantly.
